Hatim Ammor , a Moroccan singer and actor, was born on August 29 , 1981 in the Moroccan city ​​of Casablanca . His career and the emergence of his artistic talent began with his victory in the Studio 2ME season 2005 competition , and he won the admiration of the public during and after the competition. He also auditioned for the role of Hood in the Ramadan series My Girlfriend . Among his most famous songs, he called me your hug, my mother, from the words of the great Egyptian poet Khaled Al-Shaibani, composed by Hani Ismail and produced by Alam Al-Fan.
The "Africa Music Award" competition nominated Hatem Ammour to win the award for best singer in North Africa, after his song "Alawal" was chosen as the best song of 2016.
He recently released an international song with Enrique Iglesius.

